Keep a Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.
This project adheres to Semantic Versioning: https://semver.org/

Unreleased
- Added
    - New Analytics panel: fleet uptime, average repair time, and service throughput charts.
    - Role-based access control: Admin, Manager, Technician with configurable permissions.
    - CSV export for job lists and invoices.
    - Bulk actions in the Jobs table (assign, change status, export).
- Changed
    - Refactored frontend to modular components and centralized state for faster load and easier maintenance.
    - Updated API endpoints to v2 (backward compatible) and added pagination to list endpoints.
    - UI/UX improvements: responsive layout, clearer form validation messages.
- Fixed
    - Resolved intermittent race condition when creating jobs from templates.
    - Fixed timezone handling for scheduled jobs and reports.
    - Corrected sorting behavior in the Vehicles table.
- Security
    - Bumped dependencies: express, react, sequelize to address known vulnerabilities.
    - Enforced CSP headers and tightened cookie flags.

1.2.0 - 2025-09-15
- Added
    - Notifications center for job updates and alerts.
    - Audit log for critical actions (user changes, billing edits).
- Changed
    - Optimized database queries for reports, reducing report generation time by ~60%.
- Fixed
    - Fixed broken file uploads for large attachments (>10MB).
    - Fixed incorrect tax calculation on some invoice scenarios.

1.1.0 - 2025-06-01
- Added
    - Initial invoicing module: draft invoices, preview, and PDF export.
    - Vehicle maintenance schedule and reminders.
- Changed
    - Improved search across jobs, customers, and vehicles.
- Fixed
    - Resolved UI clipping on smaller screens.
    - Fixed session timeout handling.

1.0.0 - 2025-01-10
- Added
    - Initial public release: core admin dashboard features (jobs, customers, vehicles, basic settings).
    - Authentication and user management.
    - Basic reporting (jobs per day, revenue summary).

Unreleased notes:
- Follow semantic versioning. Tag releases in Git and update this file prior to publishing.
- Use this changelog for release notes and deploy summaries.